        &lt;p&gt;The administration claims these funds are being withheld due to fraud concerns, but critics argue that this is a politically motivated move to target and undermine Democratic-led states. If there are legitimate concerns about fraud, cutting funding to the needy is not the way to address it. Imagine if someone identified fraud in the Social Security program and responded by simply stopping payments to retired Americans. While that might eliminate the fraud, it would also cause immense suffering to those who depend on these programs. The same holds true for this shameful move by the Trump regime.&lt;/p&gt;
