&lt;p&gt;Recap of this week in the revolution: Kilmar Abrego Garcia free again. Trump regime&amp;#39;s exposes its own hypocrisy. U.S. citizenship on sale now and U.S. military seizes Venezuelan oil tanker. Beware of surveillance pricing when shopping online.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;section class=&quot;block the-good&quot;&gt;
	&lt;h4&gt;The good...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Kilmar Abrego Garcia freed from immigration detention &lt;a href=&quot;https://apnews.com/article/abrego-garcia-el-salvador-deportation-31160936c51932f74b717eb1143edd55&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Kilmar Abrego Garcia, 2025&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/uwXNjfjBMC-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;247&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Kilmar Abrego Garcia, from his meeting with Senator Chris Van Hollen on April 17, 2025, in El Salvador.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;On March 12, Kilmar Abrego Garcia was arrested by a DHS agent. Three days later, he was sent to a torture prison in El Salvador despite a court order specifically prohibiting his deportation to El Salvador. Despite the fact that he was &quot;accidentally&quot; deported, the Trump regime refused to bring him back to his home in the United States and falsely claimed that he was a member of a terrorist organization. The Supreme Court ordered the regime to effectuate Abrego Garcia&#39;s return. The Trump regime still refused to take action to bring Abrego Garcia home. They fought against the ruling, but after months of failed arguments and unaccepted excuses, they did arrange to bring Abrego Garcia back to the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;But the persecution didn&#39;t stop there. The Trump regime doubled-down on their false allegations that Abrego Garcia was a member of a terrorist organization and when he was returned to the United States, it was to face criminal charges. He remained in prison for several months before being returned to his home state of Maryland. Three days later, he was detained again at a routine check-in, and has been imprisoned since then while the Trump regime has repeatedly threatened to deport him to any country other than El Salvador.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;This week, Abrego Garcia&#39;s habeas petition was granted and a federal judge ordered his release from custody. But Kilmar Abrego Garcia is one of the most blatant examples of the Trump regime&#39;s incompetence and cruelty, so there is no doubt that they will try again to find some excuse to continue his persecution.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Related Links:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;ul class=&quot;related-links&quot;&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://apnews.com/article/abrego-garcia-el-salvador-deportation-31160936c51932f74b717eb1143edd55&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;(AP) Kilmar Abrego Garcia freed from federal immigration detention on judge&#39;s order and returns home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;/ul&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;hr style=&quot;clear:both&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;

&lt;section class=&quot;block the-bad&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The bad...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        The hypocrisy of the Trump regime would be laughable if it weren&#39;t so embarrassing &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.propublica.org/article/trump-mortgage-fraud-florida-principal-residences&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Caricature of Donald Trump with a sign reading &#39;Liar&#39;&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/nKuCCTrb5K-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;130&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com/users/zichrini-3417353/?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=2483441&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hanna&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com//?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=2483441&quot; target=&quot;blank&quot;&gt;Pixabay&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Donny 2-Dolls has accused several of his political enemies of mortgage fraud for listing more than one primary residence on their mortgage applications. He called the act &quot;crooked,&quot; and &quot;deceitful and potentially criminal.&quot; But Trump&#39;s use of this accusation to attempt to bully his political enemies only exposes his own hypocrisy: He has committed this same crime himself, buying multiple properties and claiming them each as primary residences simultaneously, even though he was working with leasing companies to rent out the properties as soon as the purchases were complete.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;blockquote&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Given Trump’s position on situations like this, he’s going to either need to fire himself or refer himself to the Department of Justice.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;Trump has deemed that this type of misrepresentation is sufficient to preclude someone from serving the country.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;figcaption class=&quot;blockquote-footer&quot;&gt;Kathleen Engel, Suffolk University Law Professor and Mortgage Finance Expert&lt;/figcaption&gt;
		&lt;/blockquote&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Transportation Secretary Sean Duffy has exposed his own hypocrisy in a similar way. In 2015, then a representative from Wisconsin, wrote a lengthy legal brief in which he articulated a strong and compelling argument defending the role of Congress as a check on the president, arguing, &quot;[Congress] may not bestow upon the Executive its own exclusive power of the purse,&quot; and that among the founders of the nation there was &quot;unanimous agreement that Congress, not the President, should control the purse.&quot; These words directly oppose Duffy&#39;s actions in his current role. Rather than respecting Congress&#39; power of the purse, he is attempting to restrict congressionally-appropriated transportation funding. The Government Accountability Office has already concluded that Duffy&#39;s Department of Transportation had broken the law by halting payments for electric car charging stations Congress had already approved. Duffy is now trying to put conditions on state funding for transportation infrastructure based on the state&#39;s willingness to help persecute immigrants.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;These are just some examples of the blatant hypocrisy demonstrated daily by the Trump regime. While it is highly unlikely that any of these actions will be punished, it is important to continually bring them to light to remind us of why these people have no right to hold positions of leadership or authority within our country. In the same way and for the same reasons that our founders &lt;a href=&quot;https://free-the-people.us/charters-of-freedom/declaration-of-independence/&quot;&gt;declared&lt;/a&gt; that King George III had no legal authority to rule the American colonies, we &lt;a href=&quot;https://free-the-people.us/about/resolution/&quot;&gt;declare&lt;/a&gt; that the Trump regime has no legal authority to rule the United States of America.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
