            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;While the United States is actively provoking a war with Venezuela, Donny 2-Dolls accepts a fake &quot;peace prize&quot; made up by the International Federation of Football Associations (FIFA).&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The United States has seized a commercial oil tanker off the coast of Venezuela, and armed members of the Coast Guard boarded and took control of the ship by fast-roping off of helicopters hovering just off the deck of the ship.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Taking over a merchant ship outside our own coastal waters is unusual, and a violation of international law. The Trump regime is claiming the oil tanker is &quot;involved in an illicit oil shipping network supporting foreign terrorist organizations.&quot; As usual, they are not offering any evidence of their claims. The excuse is wearing a bit thin, as the regime has been labeling everything it opposes as terrorism. Immigrants residing in our country (legally or not) are being labeled terrorists. That was the case with Kilmar Abrego Garcia, who was deported and imprisoned due to a clerical error before the regime retroactively claimed, without evidence, he belonged to a terrorist organization. Venezuelan boats have been bombed in international waters, killing dozens of people who the regime is claiming, also without evidence, belong to narco-terrorist groups (Whatever that means). Now commercial oil tankers are being seized by our military using the same flimsy claims.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The truth is, none of this has anything to do with terrorism or drug trafficking or defending the United States from imaginary threats. It is all about Trump&#39;s plan to overthrow Venezuelan president, Nicolás Maduro. Not because Maduro may have stolen the election in 2024, or because he is acting as a dictator, but because many of the Venezuelans whe have fled the country&#39;s political and economic situation have sought asylum (legally) in the United States. And let&#39;s not forget that Venezuela has the world&#39;s largest oil reserves, and the United States has a long history of fighting wars to control the international flow of oil. Trump has even stated that there is likely to be a ground invasion of Venezuela starting soon, though there is no reasonable legal justification for such an invasion of a sovereign nation.&lt;/p&gt;
