        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Unbalanced&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/hpLQ5N2De7-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;224&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com/users/josephvm-289221/?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=4758087&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Joseph V M&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://pixabay.com//?utm_source=link-attribution&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_campaign=image&amp;utm_content=4758087&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Pixabay&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;A federal judge has dismissed the Trump regime&#39;s cases against Letitia James and James Comey. After Halligan&#39;s disastrous bungling of the case against Comey last week, you might think the cases were thrown out because of something she did wrong, but it wasn&#39;t &lt;i&gt;how&lt;/i&gt; the cases were handled that was the problem. It was &lt;i&gt;who&lt;/i&gt; was handling them.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;It turns out that Lindsey Halligan&#39;s appointment to the position of US Attorney for the Eastern District of Virginia was unlawful. Halligan was appointed as an interim U.S. attorney by Pam Bondi as ordered by Donny 2-Dolls via social media post. But the Attorney General does not have the authority to make such an appointment. Only federal judges in the district in question can make an interim appointment to serve until the vacancy can be filled.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The case against Letitia James could be restarted once the US Attorney for the Eastern District of Virginia is properly appointed, but the statute of limitations has expired in the case against James Comey, meaning there can be no further indictment.&lt;/p&gt;
