&lt;section class=&quot;block the-bad&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The bad...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Trump regime&#39;s bungling could cause massive corporate losses &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.courthousenews.com/penny-shortages-causing-big-legal-business-headaches-in-much-of-us/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;A pile of pennies&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/Q3bD_ra3OL-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;112&quot;&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;For years, the United States has been considering abandoning the penny because it costs more to mint that it&#39;s worth. Other countries facing similar issues have opted to make their low-value coins out of cheaper materials or eliminate them altogether. But either way, they planned for the inevitable consequences.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Not the Trump regime, though. They just decided to stop minting the penny, and provided no explanations, nor any rules or guidelines for how future transactions should be handled. Many states have laws saying credit card customers can&#39;t be charged less for a purchase than cash customers, so businesses can&#39;t just round up their transactions to the nearest nickel without facing potential lawsuits. And if they round all their transactions down, they stand to lose millions of dollars in revenue.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Then there&#39;s the banks...if they cash a check and don&#39;t have exact change, they are required to round &lt;i&gt;up,&lt;/i&gt; not down so they don&#39;t short-change the customer. Same goes for businesses that pay employees in cash.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;And on, and on, and on, all throughout our already-crumbling economy.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;blockquote&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;They just said &#39;Let&#39;s get rid of it&#39; and moved on, but they&#39;ve created a train wreck...&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;p&gt;There&#39;s been no announcement as to why, This was done without any planning or forethought as to what would happen and how it would cascade through the economy.&lt;/p&gt;
			&lt;figcaption class=&quot;blockquote-footer&quot;&gt;Bill Maurer, director of the University of California, Irvine&#39;s Institute for Money, Technology and Financial Inclusion&lt;/figcaption&gt;
		&lt;/blockquote&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
