		&lt;p&gt;After voting 14 times to reject the Republican continuing resolution to fund the government on the grounds that they would not consider a bill unless the Republican party was willing to extend tax credits for the Affordable care Act for 20+ million Americans to prevent their insurance premiums from doubling or tripling in 2026, several Democrats gave up and agreed to reopen the government without any such extension. This just 5 days after the election showed overwhelming support for the Democratic Party while it held the lines against the Trump regime.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The new continuing resolution proposes holding a vote on extending the ACA tax credits at some point in the future (likely after the open enrollment period has closed and Americans are stuck with their new premium increases). Why anyone would agree to just the idea of holding a vote on a purely partisan issue when Republicans have a majority of representation in both the House and Senate is beyond comprehension.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;div style=&quot;text-align:center&quot;&gt;
			&lt;iframe width=&quot;560&quot; height=&quot;315&quot; src=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/embed/eFI6MwlLJ08?si=moNlfuVdyGsuXysp&quot; title=&quot;YouTube video player&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; allow=&quot;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share&quot; referrerpolicy=&quot;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&quot; allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
