    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Assault with a sandwich? Nah. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.usatoday.com/picture-gallery/news/nation/2025/11/06/sandwich-guy-not-guilty-assault-federal-officer-cultural-moment/87132759007/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Sean Dunn, August 10, 2025&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/vNW3CRuPgL-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;211&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Sean Dunn throws a sandwich at a CBP officer in Washington D.C. on August 10, 2025.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;On August 10, Sean Dunn was captured on video in a verbal confrontation with a CBP officer in Washington D.C. A frustrated Dunn tossed his Subway sandwich at the officer and was subsequently chased down and detained. He was initially charged with felony assault, but a grand jury refused to indict him on such a ridiculous charge, so the charges were dropped to misdemeanor assault.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Dunn was found not guilty of the equally ridiculous misdemeanor charge in his trial. The defense argued that a sandwich simply cannot be wielded with sufficient force to pose a credible threat to a man wearing- a bullet proof vest.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;Dunn has become something of a symbol of the anti-Trump regime, with murals, signs, and banners depicting him throwing a sandwich appearing all around the country.&lt;/p&gt;
