            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Trump announcing tariffs for all&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/8_d_-gQcpa-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;150&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Donny 2-Dolls announcing tariffs for everyone a few days before chickening out and rolling them back. Then announcing them again. Then rolling them back...&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The Senate passed a resolution to undo many of the Trump regime&#39;s global tariffs in a 51-47 vote.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The vote was mostly passed by party lines, with all Democrats voting yes, along with 4 Republicans. The resolution nullifies the presidential declaration of a state of emergency that the Trump regime was using to justify its usurpation of Congress&#39;s authority to levy tariffs.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;But don&#39;t get excited. The Senate vote is only one step. The measure would have to be approved by the House (Which has been out of session for weeks because Johnson refuses to swear in the newest representative) and signed by Trump, and that&#39;s not going to happen.&lt;/p&gt;
