        &lt;p&gt;The aircraft carrier &lt;i&gt;USS Gerald Ford,&lt;/i&gt; the largest warship in the United States Navy, is making its way to the Caribbean Sea near Venezuela. Meanwhile, the guided missile destroyer &lt;i&gt;USS Gravely&lt;/i&gt; is docked in Trinidad and Tobago.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Venezuealan President Maduro has denounced the United States, calling these deployments and the wanton destruction of Venezuelan watercraft in international waters an attempt by the United States to fabricate an &quot;eternal war&quot; against his country.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;To date, the United States has killed at least 43 Venezuelans in international waters, claiming that they are smuggling drugs into the United States, but not offering any evidence to support those claims.&lt;/p&gt;
