&lt;h4&gt;Keeping you informed...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Shutdown updates: House continues to be paid for not working, military and ICE are being paid illegally, and SNAP benefits for the needy set to expire &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.govtrack.us/posts/550/2025-10-24_you-are-here&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Government Shutdown, 2025&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/na3wOt70L8-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;133&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.flickr.com/people/169738192@N02&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kaz Vorpal&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Government_Shutdown_(32905547137).png&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; Licensed under the &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 2.0 Generic license&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Federal workers nationwide are missing their paychecks while the government remains shut down with no end in sight. Some of these workers still have to show up to work every day, but most do not.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The House of Representatives, on the other hand, continues to be paid. But they aren&#39;t showing up for work, since the House has been out of session since September 19. The Senate convenes a few times a week and votes on the continuing resolution proposed by the House, which they continue to reject.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The standoff continues, and if it continues into next week (which it probably will), it will become the longest government shutdown in the history of the United States. The current record for the longest government shutdown was from December 22, 2018 to January 25, 2019 (during Donny 2-Dolls&#39; first term as president).&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;The standoff continues, with Democrats holding out for extensions of healthcare subsidies for the Affordable Care Act to prevent a doubling or tripling of healthcare premiums for millions of Americans. The Republicans refuse to make any concessions or negotiate on a new continuing resolution to get the government funded again.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Due to the shutdown, Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP) benefits have been cut off as of November 1. This means that, in addition to millions of government workers not being paid, tens of millions of Americans will start to go hungry as the holiday season begins.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Military members did get paid on October 15th and 31st through an illegal allocation of funds that was not authorized by Congress. ICE-stapo agents are also being paid through illegal allocations of funds.&lt;/p&gt;
