&lt;section class=&quot;block info&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Keeping you informed...&lt;/h4&gt;
	&lt;div class=&quot;blob&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-title&quot;&gt;
        Could Mamdani mark the birth of a new People&#39;s Democratic Party? &lt;a href=&quot;https://robertreich.substack.com/p/the-mamdani-moment&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Zohran Mamdani, 2024&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/_gKmPRBYn6-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;300&quot;&gt;
            &lt;p class=&quot;caption&quot;&gt;Image by Karamccurdy from &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:New_York_State_Assemblymember_Zohran_Mamdani.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Wikimedia Commons.&lt;/a&gt; Licensed under the &lt;a href=&quot;https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/deed.en&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 4.0 International license&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Despite bipartisan attacks against Zohran Mamdani (described above), he has a chance to fundamentally rebuild the dysfunctional Democratic Party into a people&#39;s party that can stand up to the Trump regime.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Mamdani&#39;s campaign is built on an understanding of what the people of New York need and want for their city. His proposed solutions to fixing New York City are bold and daring, but simple and straightforward. There are no talks about offering tax credits with strict eligibility requirements, complicated plans that no one understands rolling out over decades, or vague promises of a better tomorrow. Instead, he is tackling the everyday problems faced by New Yorkers, centering around one simple rallying cry: New York is too expensive. And he has plans to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;His plans include offering free public transit, free child care, a four-year rent freeze, and a $30 minimum wage. Can he do all that? No one knows. But there&#39;s one thing we all do know: It&#39;s about time someone at least &lt;i&gt;tried&lt;/i&gt; to do it. And if he can do it and it doesn&#39;t fix the problems, he&#39;s the kind of person who will try something else until he gets it right.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;More important that what Mamdani is proposing or whether he succeeds or fails is the simple fact that he is inspiring a new generation of Americans. Young New Yorkers are flocking to support his campaign because they believe in him and his vision for their future. And Mamdani is threatening the status quo within his own party. Corporate Democrats who claim to represent the working class and defend the poor without delivering any real solutions have no chance of standing up to a well-loved candidate who actually delivers results for his constituents.&lt;/p&gt;
