        Trump hands the reigns of his undeclared war on Venezuela to...Stephen Miller? &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2025/sep/29/stephen-miller-venezuela-drug-boat-strike&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;[Link&lt;span class=&quot;bi bi-link-45deg&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;]&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;blob-content&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;image-right&quot; style=&quot;width:225px&quot;&gt;
            &lt;img class=&quot;img-link&quot; alt=&quot;Venezuelan boat destroyed by US military in international waters&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; decoding=&quot;async&quot; style=&quot;--img-width:200&quot; src=&quot;/images/9_n7YiEKRo-200.webp&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; height=&quot;117&quot;&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The United States has been destroying Venezuelan watercraft in international water on the unsubstantiated claims that they are carrying narcotics, and White House deputy chief of staff Stephen Miller has played a leading role in directing the attacks, which are carried out by the United States armed forces.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;The Trump regime has been claiming that these actions are taken in self-defense, though legal experts allege that they are, instead, extrajudicial murders that take place in international waters.&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
