        &lt;p&gt;Protesters have gathered every day to hold a prayer vigil outside this facility every week for more than &lt;b&gt;twenty years&lt;/b&gt;. Under the Trump regime, ICE agents have grown more violent towards both detainees and protesters, and the Broadview police department has gone from defending protesters to defending ICE agents, and is now turning a blind eye to the increasing violence. Protesters have been shot with pepperballs and rubber bullets, teargassed, thrown to the streets, and agents have driven their cars through crowds of people on public streets.&lt;/p&gt;
